23/07/2004
BELGRADE. 
Serbia-Montenegro -- Federal Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic said on Thursday (22 July) that he would urge the federal government to drop its lawsuit against NATO member states. 
Serbia-Montenegro is suing several NATO members for the 1999 bombing of Belgrade. 
Draskovic says dropping the suit is an important precondition for eventual Euro-Atlantic integration. 
(B92 - 22/07/04)
